Challenges and Objectives

To support our clients vision of building an advanced Remote Patient Monitoring (RPM) platform, Intellivon partnered to overcome critical challenges and deliver a secure, AI-powered healthcare solution. This collaboration centered on the following core objectives:

Develop intelligent algorithms for early disease detection, anomaly detection in vitals, risk stratification, NLP-driven insights, and adherence prediction to enable proactive, personalized interventions.
Build scalable, cross-platform applications seamlessly integrating with IoT-enabled medical devices to support continuous patient monitoring and provider dashboards with real-time health trend visualization.
Implement OAuth 2.0, OpenID Connect, and end-to-end compliance with HIPAA, GDPR, and SOC 2 to safeguard sensitive patient health data.
Leverage AWS cloud infrastructure for high availability, scalability, and operational efficiency, supported by extensive unit, integration, and security testing.
Deliver comprehensive documentation, staff training, and intuitive design to ensure seamless adoption, ease of use, and long-term operational success.

Solutions

The Intellivon Approach

Intellivon executed a robust strategy, leveraging SMART on FHIR integration, AI-powered analytics, and secure cloud deployment to transform the clients Remote Patient Monitoring (RPM) platform, redefining standards for digital healthcare delivery.

Developed advanced algorithms for early disease detection, anomaly detection in vitals, patient risk stratification, NLP-driven insights, and adherence prediction.
Engineered HIPAA-compliant applications with IoT device connectivity, enabling continuous patient monitoring and provider dashboards for real-time health visualization.
Deployed the platform in a scalable AWS environment with built-in resilience, high availability, and compliance-ready infrastructure.
Integrated OAuth 2.0, OpenID Connect, and compliance with HIPAA, GDPR, and SOC 2 to safeguard sensitive patient information.

Real Results

The SMART on FHIRenabled RPM solution significantly enhanced healthcare delivery, shifting workflows from manual entry to real-time, AI-driven patient care that improved outcomes, efficiency, and provider satisfaction.

Seamless Epic EHR integration reduced manual data entry time by 68%, freeing providers to focus more on patient care.
Real-time device updates improved care team responsiveness by 64% faster, enabling faster interventions and treatment adjustments.
AI-powered risk detection identified high-risk patients with 87% accuracy, supporting earlier interventions and improved clinical outcomes.
Positive provider feedback reflected a 72% boost in patient engagement, with smoother workflows and stronger care coordination.
Strong security and compliance measures ensured 100% adherence to HIPAA, GDPR, and SOC 2, safeguarding patient data integrity.
